                    <msContents>
                        <summary>48–49 seem to deal with the business of the Petra church. In 48 the document in question is described as a receipt and many words appearing in the fragments suggest that the document(s) dealt mainly with the ﬁnances of the church, possibly a lease of an agricultural land. Terms related to taxes are also frequent. The reconstruction of 48–49 is complicated by many irregularities.</summary>
                        <msItemStruct>
                            <note type="general">All fragments are written transversa charta across the ﬁbers, except for fragment series C10 not included in the reconstructions, which was written in columns. Several individual hands appear in the fragments, most of them probably belonging to signatures, but the presence of more than one scribe is also possible, since there might be multiple documents.</note>
                            <note type="general">Reproduced in plates LXXI–LXXIII of volume IV</note>
                            <note type="local_note">Field no. VI.1 (C fragments)</note>
